mu1 <- 0  # X1 
mu2 <- 0  # X2 

s11 <- 1  # X1 
s22 <- 1  # X2 
s12 <- 0.5  # X1 X2 
rho <- 0.5  # X1 X2 

x1 <- seq(-3.1, 3.1, length=51)  #  X1 
x2 <- x1  #  X2 


f <- function(x1, x2){  #   
  term1 = 1/(2*pi*sqrt(s11*s22*(1-rho^2)))
  term2 = -1/(2*(1-rho^2))
  term3 = (x1-mu1)^2/s11
  term4 = (x2-mu2)^2/s22
  term5 = 2*rho*(((x1-mu1)/sqrt(s11))*((x2-mu2)/sqrt(s22)))
  
  term1*exp(term2*(term3+term4-term5))
}

z = outer(x1,x2,f)  # outer() x1 x2   f   
length(z)  #  51      51*51 z  
[1] 2601
persp(x1,x2,z, main="Two dimensional Normal Distribution", 
      theta=45, phi=25, col=gray(.8), zlab="f(x)")  # theta phi  , ? 

contour(x1,x2,z, main="Contour plot")  #

sk <- function(x){
  n <- dim(x)[1]  #  
  p <- dim(x)[2]  #  
  
  m <- colMeans(x)  # 
  
  S <- cov(x)  # 
  S <- (n-1)/n*S  #  (MLE)
  S.inv <- solve(S)  #   
  
  g <- matrix(rep(NA,n*n), ncol=n)  # g 
  # g 
  for(i in 1:n){
    for(j in 1:n){
      g[i,j] <- t(x[i,]-m) %*% S.inv %*% (x[j,]-m)
    }
  }
  
  b1 <- sum(g^3)/n^2  # 
  b2 <- sum(diag(g)^2)/n  # 
  
  result <- c(b1, b2)
  names(result) <- c("", "") 
  return(result)
}

sk <- function(x){
  n <- dim(x)[1]  #  
  p <- dim(x)[2]  #  
  
  m <- colMeans(x)  # 
  
  S <- cov(x)  # 
  S <- (n-1)/n*S  #  (MLE)
  S.inv <- solve(S)  #   
  
  g <- matrix(rep(NA,n*n), ncol=n)  # g 
  # g 
  for(i in 1:n){
    for(j in 1:n){
      g[i,j] <- t(x[i,]-m) %*% S.inv %*% (x[j,]-m)
    }
  }
  
  b1 <- sum(g^3)/n^2  # 
  b2 <- sum(diag(g)^2)/n  # 
  
  result <- c(b1, b2)
  names(result) <- c("", "") 
  return(result)
}
